{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":152007,"duration_api_ms":151919,"num_turns":5,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"a627ba42-079e-4ea5-a204-08aee6f32974","total_cost_usd":0.4637645,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":30605,"cache_read_input_tokens":116690,"output_tokens":3897,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":30605,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":5,"outputTokens":3897,"cacheReadInputTokens":116690,"cacheCreationInputTokens":30605,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.34707625000000003,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000},"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":99,"outputTokens":7196,"cacheReadInputTokens":416680,"cacheCreationInputTokens":31153,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.11668825000000002,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"summary":"All four amendments identify genuine issues in the task-run lineage code. Amendment fr-2-0432d582 is a straightforward observability fix. Amendment fr-2-95143b50 identifies a real crash-consistency gap across three independent durable writes. Amendments fr-2-31529cd0 and fr-2-babd2df3 both stem from the same root cause — legacy paired-row NDJSON data not being collapsed — manifesting as duplicate results in find_runs_for_bead and false ambiguity errors in update_task_run respectively. I agree with the planner positions on all four.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-2-0432d582","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified in fs.rs:2472-2479: the terminal-rejection error includes bead_id and project_id but omits run_id, even though (a) run_id is available as a function parameter and (b) all other error messages in the run_id-present branch (lines 2424, 2432, 2442) include `run={run_id}`. When the exact-match path at line 2407 resolves to a terminal entry, the missing run_id in the error makes it harder to debug which specific run was rejected. Adding it is safe, consistent, and directly improves diagnostics."},{"amendment_id":"fr-2-95143b50","decision":"accept","rationale":"Confirmed in service.rs:412-469: three sequential durable writes — lineage_store.update_task_run (line 412), snapshot_store.write_snapshot (line 451), journal_store.append_event (line 469) — happen without a shared transaction or recovery mechanism. A crash after step 1 (lineage shows succeeded) but before step 2 (snapshot still has stale in_progress_beads count) leaves durably inconsistent state that no current code path repairs. Since lineage is the most detailed source of truth (per-entry outcomes), a reconciliation function that reconstructs snapshot counters from it is the right mitigation. At minimum, this partial-failure mode should be documented so operators know to run reconciliation after unexpected crashes."},{"amendment_id":"fr-2-31529cd0","decision":"accept","rationale":"Confirmed in fs.rs:2500-2517: find_runs_for_bead performs a flat filter-and-sort on raw NDJSON rows with no deduplication or collapsing logic. If legacy data contains paired rows per attempt (a 'running' start row plus a terminal completion row), this function returns both, producing duplicate entries and a perpetually-stale 'running' record. The sort-by-started_at-then-finished_at doesn't resolve this since both rows share the same started_at. The function needs to collapse paired rows into a single attempt record (keeping the terminal outcome), and a regression test with synthetic legacy paired-row data should verify the behavior."},{"amendment_id":"fr-2-babd2df3","decision":"accept","rationale":"Confirmed in fs.rs:2447-2468: the no-run_id fallback path filters matching entries for non-terminal outcomes (line 2454) to find open attempts. Legacy paired-row data leaves behind 'running' start rows even for completed attempts (the terminal row is a separate entry). When a new attempt is appended, the open_matches filter picks up both the legacy orphaned 'running' row and the genuinely new 'running' row, yielding multiple matches and triggering the 'provide run_id to disambiguate' error at line 2462. This makes it impossible to finalize new attempts on beads that have legacy history without providing a run_id, even though run_id is explicitly optional. The fix is to exclude legacy start rows that have a corresponding terminal row from the open-match set, with a regression test seeding old-format paired rows."}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"5d7a60da-204c-49fb-9087-ed54e2d9a2f8"}
